{{hatnote|Not to be confused with [[BIOBASE (company)]], a German publisher of molecular biology databases.}} {{infobox bibliographic database | image = | caption = | producer = [[Elsevier]] | country = | history = 1954–present | languages = English | providers = DataStar, DIALOG, DIMDI, STN | cost = Subscription | disciplines = [[Biology]] | depth = indexing, abstracting, bibliographic citations, and separate species dictionary | formats = titles, authors, abstracts, bibliographic details and authors' addresses | temporal = 1994–present | geospatial = Worldwide coverage | number = Over 4 million | updates = Weekly | p_title = | p_dates = | ISSN = 0733-4443 | web = http://www.elsevier.com/wps/find/bibliographicdatabasedescription.cws_home/600715/description#description | titles = }} '''Elsevier BIOBASE''' is a [[bibliographic database]] covering all topics pertaining to [[biology|biological research]] throughout the world. It was established in the 1950s in print format as '''''Current Awareness in Biological Sciences'''''. Temporal coverage is from 1994 to the present. The database has over 4.1 million records as of December 2008. More than 300,000 records are added annually and 84% contain an abstract. It is updated weekly.
