'''MAGEN''' (Masking Gateway for Enterprises) is [[information security]] technology designed by [[IBM R&D Labs in Israel#Haifa Research Lab|IBM's Haifa Research Lab]].  MAGEN is designed to keep users from viewing discrete chunks of secret or sensitive data on their screens that they are not authorized to see.

MAGEN applies a sort of inverse [[highlighter|highlighting]] on the data in question in real time as it is rendered on the screen.  This allows "[[Classified information|eyes only]]" business logic to be implemented once, at the screen, rather than within each affected application.

MAGEN leverages a combination of [[optical character recognition]] and [[screen scraping]] techniques.

