The '''Michael and Kate Bárány Award''' for Young Investigators from the [[Biophysical Society]] in [[Rockville, Maryland]], "recognizes an outstanding contribution to biophysics by a person who has not achieved the rank of full professor."<ref name=awardsite>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150320172244/http://www.biophysics.org/AwardsFunding/SocietyAwards/MichaelandKateB%C3%A1r%C3%A1nyAward/tabid/504/Default.aspx|url=http://www.biophysics.org/AwardsFunding/SocietyAwards/MichaelandKateB%C3%A1r%C3%A1nyAward/tabid/504/Default.aspx|title=Michael and Kate Bárány Award (est. 1992)|archivedate=2015-03-20|publisher=Biophysical Society}}</ref> The award was established in 1992 as the '''Young Investigator Award''' and renamed in 1998, when it was endowed by Michael Bárány<ref name=michael/> and Kate Bárány.<ref name=kate/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chem.umn.edu/groups/baranygp/katebarany/MB_KB_1998_BiophysSoc_writeup.pdf|title=Michael and Kate Bárány Award for Young Investigators|first1=Sarah|last1=Hitchcock-DeGregori|publisher=Biophysical Society|year=1998|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140325165036/https://www.chem.umn.edu/groups/baranygp/katebarany/MB_KB_1998_BiophysSoc_writeup.pdf|archivedate=2014-03-25}}</ref> The Báránys were survivors of [[The Holocaust]] who went on to become leading researchers in [[muscle contraction]].<ref name=michael>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1007/s10974-012-9295-8| pmid = 22539009| title = Michael Bárány: A recollection| journal = Journal of Muscle Research and Cell Motility| volume = 33| issue = 6| pages = 373–6| year = 2012| last1 = Chalovich | first1 = J. M. }}</ref><ref name=kate>{{cite web|archivedate=2014-08-01|title=Kate Bárány (1929-2011)|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140801042022/http://www.chem.umn.edu/groups/baranygp/katebarany/ |url=http://www.chem.umn.edu/groups/baranygp/katebarany/|publisher=University of Minnesota}}</ref>
